      "subject": "Solid Mechanics",
      "topic": "Column Buckling",
      "difficulty": "hard",
      "type": "NAT",
      "stem": "A pin-ended steel column ($E=200\\,\\text{GPa}$) is a solid circular section of diameter $40\\,\\text{mm}$ and length $3\\,\\text{m}$. The Euler critical load is _____ kN.",
      "answer": 27.5611,
      "tolerance": 1,
      "solution": "**Concept.** $P_{cr}=\\dfrac{\\pi^2 EI}{L^2}$ (both ends pinned), $I=\\dfrac{\\pi d^4}{64}$.\n\n**Working.**\n$$I=\\dfrac{\\pi\\,40^4}{64}=125664\\,\\text{mm}^4,\\quad P_{cr}=\\dfrac{\\pi^2\\times 200000\\times 125664}{3000^2}=27.6\\,\\text{kN}.$$\n\n**Answer.** $27.6\\,\\text{kN}$",
      "archetype": "C",
      "marks": 2
